Banks to Settle Mortgage-Bond Fraud Charges With SEC, WSJ Says

-- B y   V i v e k   S h a n k a r
-- 
2011-04-15T02:44:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/banks-to-settle-mortgage-bond-fraud-charges-with-sec-wsj-says.html
JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) ,  Citigroup
Inc. (C) , Morgan Stanley are among banks close to settling
allegations of fraud brought by the U.S. Securities and Exchange
Commission related to mortgage-bond deals, the Wall Street
Journal reported, citing unidentified people familiar with the
matter.  All the banks declined to comment, the newspaper said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Vivek Shankar at 
 vshankar3@bloomberg.net  